# File Structure

## Project Organization

```
shacdn/
├── .cursor/
│   └── rules/              # Cursor AI rules (this folder)
├── docs/                   # All documentation
│   ├── COMPONENT_GUIDE.md
│   └── PROJECT_SUMMARY.md
├── src/
│   ├── components/         # All UI components
│   │   ├── Alert/
│   │   │   ├── Alert.tsx
│   │   │   └── Alert.module.scss
│   │   ├── Button/
│   │   │   ├── Button.tsx
│   │   │   └── Button.module.scss
│   │   └── [22 more components...]
│   ├── styles/             # Global styles & variables
│   │   ├── variables.scss  # Design tokens
│   │   └── globals.scss    # Global styles
│   ├── App.tsx             # Demo page
│   ├── App.module.scss
│   └── main.tsx
├── README.md               # Quick start guide
├── package.json
└── vite.config.ts
```

## Component Folder Pattern

Each component MUST have:
1. `ComponentName.tsx` - React component
2. `ComponentName.module.scss` - Scoped styles

Optional:
- Sub-components in same file (Card has CardHeader, CardContent, etc.)
- Types can be exported from same .tsx file

## Import Organization

Order imports as:
1. External libraries (React, etc.)
2. Internal components
3. Styles (always last)

```tsx
import { forwardRef, type HTMLAttributes } from 'react';
import { OtherComponent } from '../OtherComponent/OtherComponent';
import styles from './Component.module.scss';
```

## Documentation Location

- `docs/COMPONENT_GUIDE.md` - Component usage guide
- `docs/PROJECT_SUMMARY.md` - Project overview
- `README.md` - Quick start only

Do NOT create documentation outside these files.
